This is a textbook case of **coverage-without-verification** — every method is exercised but almost nothing is actually asserted. Here's the severity-ranked audit:

---

## 🔴 Critical — Missing Assertions (tests pass even if behavior is wrong)

### 1. `AddProduct_Works` (line 17) — **Zero assertions**
Calls `AddProduct` but never verifies the product was stored.
```csharp
// Fix: verify the product is retrievable
_catalog.AddProduct(product);
var stored = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNotNull(stored);
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", stored.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, stored.Price);
```

### 2. `UpdatePrice_Works` (line 32) — **Zero assertions**
Calls `UpdatePrice` but never checks the price actually changed. A no-op `Save()` would pass this test.
```csharp
// Fix: verify the new price
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
```

### 3. `RemoveProduct_Works` (line 38) — **Zero assertions**
Calls `RemoveProduct` but never checks the product is gone. A no-op `Delete()` would pass.
```csharp
// Fix: verify deletion
_catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
```

### 4. `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (line 68) — **Zero assertions**
Applies a 10% discount but never checks any price changed. The core arithmetic (`Price * (1 - fraction)`) is completely unverified.
```csharp
// Fix: verify discounted prices
_catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);
Assert.AreEqual(8.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")!.Price);
Assert.AreEqual(17.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-002")!.Price);
```

### 5. `ImportFromCsv_Works` (line 85) — **Zero assertions**
Imports CSV but never checks any product was created. Parsing bugs (e.g., wrong column order, decimal format) would go undetected.
```csharp
// Fix: verify imported product
_catalog.ImportFromCsv("SKU-001,Widget,9.99");
var imported = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNotNull(imported);
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", imported.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, imported.Price);
```

### 6. `GetProductCount_Works` (line 63) — **Zero assertions, also wrong setup**
Doesn't add any products before calling `GetProductCount`, so it only tests the empty-catalog path. The result is discarded.
