**Root cause:** Every test follows the same template — call the method, optionally `Assert.IsNotNull` on the return value, done. This inflates line/branch coverage to ~95% while verifying almost nothing. A `Save()` that silently drops data, a discount formula that doubles prices, or a CSV export in the wrong format would all pass this suite green.
